items.name: weapon_deagle
items.item_description: As expensive as it is powerful, the Desert Eagle is an iconic pistol that is difficult to master but surprisingly accurate at long range.

items.name: weapon_elite
items.item_description: Firing two large-mag Berettas at once will lower accuracy and increase load times. On the bright side, you'll get to fire two large-mag Berettas at once.

items.name: weapon_fiveseven
items.item_description: Highly accurate and armor-piercing, the pricy Five-Seven is a slow-loader that compensates with a generous 20-round magazine and forgiving recoil.

items.name: weapon_glock
items.item_description: The Glock 18 is a serviceable first-round pistol that works best against unarmored opponents and is capable of firing three-round bursts.

items.name: weapon_ak47
items.item_description: Powerful and reliable, the AK-47 is one of the most popular assault rifles in the world. It is most deadly in short, controlled bursts of fire.

items.name: weapon_aug
items.item_description: Powerful and accurate, the AUG scoped assault rifle compensates for its long reload times with low spread and a high rate of fire.

items.name: weapon_awp
items.item_description: High risk and high reward, the infamous AWP is recognizable by its signature report and one-shot, one-kill policy.

items.name: weapon_famas
items.item_description: A cheap option for cash-strapped players, the FAMAS effectively fills the niche between more expensive rifles and the less-effective SMGs.

items.name: weapon_g3sg1
items.item_description: The pricy G3SG1 lowers movement speed considerably but compensates with a higher rate of fire than other sniper rifles.

items.name: weapon_galilar
items.item_description: A less expensive option among the terrorist-exclusive assault rifles, the Galil AR is a serviceable weapon in medium to long-range combat.

items.name: weapon_m249
items.item_description: A strong open-area LMG, the M249 is the perfect choice for players willing to trade a slow fire rate for increased accuracy and a high ammo capacity.

items.name: weapon_m4a1
items.item_description: More accurate but less damaging than its AK-47 counterpart, the M4A4 is the full-auto assault rifle of choice for CTs.

items.name: weapon_mac10
items.item_description: Essentially a box that bullets come out of, the MAC-10 SMG boasts a high rate of fire, with poor spread accuracy and high recoil as trade-offs.

items.name: weapon_p90
items.item_description: Easily recognizable for its unique bullpup design, the P90 a great weapon to shoot on the move due to its high-capacity magazine and low recoil.

items.name: weapon_ump45
items.item_description: The misunderstood middle child of the SMG family, the UMP45's small magazine is the only drawback to an otherwise versatile close-quarters automatic.

items.name: weapon_xm1014
items.item_description: The XM1014 is a powerful fully automatic shotgun that justifies its heftier price tag with the ability to paint a room with lead fast.

items.name: weapon_bizon
items.item_description: The Bizon SMG is low-damage, but offers a uniquely designed high-capacity drum magazine that reloads quickly.

items.name: weapon_mag7
items.item_description: The CT-exclusive Mag-7 delivers a devastating amount of damage at close range. Its rapid magazine-style reloads make it a great tactical choice.

items.name: weapon_negev
items.item_description: The high-mag, fast-firing Negev is the perfect weapon for spraying a lot of rounds quickly, with a hefty price tag, high spread and frustrating recoil as trade-offs.

items.name: weapon_sawedoff
items.item_description: The classic Sawed-Off deals very heavy close-range damage, but with its low accuracy, high spread and slow rate of fire, you'd better kill what you hit.

items.name: weapon_tec9
items.item_description: A low-accuracy semi-automatic, the Tec-9 offers excellent penetration damage and a high magazine capacity, though its recoil can be unforgiving.

items.name: weapon_taser
items.item_description: Perfect for close-range ambushes and enclosed area encounters, the single-shot x27 Zeus is capable of incapacitating an enemy in a single hit.

items.name: weapon_hkp2000
items.item_description: Accurate and controllable, the German-made P2000 is a serviceable first-round pistol that works best against unarmored opponents.

items.name: weapon_mp7
items.item_description: Versatile but expensive, the German-made MP7 SMG is the perfect choice for high-impact close-range combat.

items.name: weapon_mp9
items.item_description: Manufactured in Switzerland, the cutting-edge MP9 SMG is an ergonomic polymer weapon favored by private security firms.

items.name: weapon_nova
items.item_description: The Nova's rock-bottom price tag makes it a great ambush weapon for a cash-strapped team.

items.name: weapon_p250
items.item_description: A low-recoil firearm with a high rate of fire, the P250 is a relatively inexpensive choice against armored opponents.

items.name: weapon_scar20
items.item_description: The SCAR-20 is a semi-automatic sniper rifle that trades a high rate of fire and powerful long-distance damage for sluggish movement speed and big price tag.

items.name: weapon_sg556
items.item_description: The terrorist-exclusive SG553 is a premium scoped alternative to the AK47 for effective long-range engagement.

items.name: weapon_ssg08
items.item_description: The SSG08 bolt-action is a low-damage but very cost-effective sniper rifle, making it a smart choice for early-round long-range marksmanship.

items.name: weapon_knife
items.item_description: Quiet and always available, the knife has a fast, low-damage primary attack and a slow, high-damage secondary attack. A backstab will earn quiet players an instant kill.

items.name: weapon_flashbang
items.item_description: The non-lethal flashbang grenade temporarily blinds anybody within its concussive blast, making it perfect for flushing out closed-in areas. Its loud explosion also temporarily masks the sound of footsteps.

items.name: weapon_hegrenade
items.item_description: The high explosive fragmentation grenade administers high damage through a wide area, making it ideal for clearing out hostile rooms.

items.name: weapon_smokegrenade
items.item_description: The smoke grenade creates a medium-area smoke screen. It can effectively hide your team from snipers, or even just create a useful distraction.

items.name: weapon_molotov
items.item_description: The Molotov is a powerful and unpredictable area denial weapon that bursts into flames when thrown on the ground, injuring any player in its radius.

items.name: weapon_decoy
items.item_description: When thrown, the decoy grenade emulates the sound of the most powerful weapon you are carrying, creating the illusion of additional supporting forces.

items.name: weapon_incgrenade
items.item_description: When thrown, the incendiary grenade releases a high-temperature chemical reaction capable of burning anyone within its wide blast radius.

items.name: weapon_c4
items.item_description: Stable and resistant to most physical shocks, this improvised plastic explosive has a detonation velocity of over 8,000 miles per second when ignited.

items.name: weapon_knife_t
items.item_description: Quiet and always available, the knife has a fast, low-damage primary attack and a slow, high-damage secondary attack. A backstab will earn quiet players an instant kill.

items.name: weapon_m4a1_silencer
items.item_description: Less expensive and with a smaller magazine than its unmuffled counterpart, the silenced M4A1 provides quieter shots with less recoil and better accuracy.

items.name: weapon_usp_silencer
items.item_description: A fan favorite from Counter-Strike Source, the Silenced USP Pistol has a detachable silencer that gives shots less recoil while suppressing attention-getting noise.

items.name: Recipe Trade Up
items.item_description: In exchange for 10 items from the same Collection and of identical quality, you will receive a single item from that Collection of a quality one higher than the items you provided.

items.name: weapon_cz75a
items.item_description: A fully automatic variant of the CZ75, the CZ75-Auto is another inexpensive choice against armored opponents. But with very little ammo provided, strong trigger discipline is required.

items.name: weapon_bayonet
items.item_description: Relatively unchanged in its design since World War II, the bayonet still retains a place in modern military strategy. Bayonet charges have continued to be effective as recently as the second Gulf War and the war in Afghanistan.

items.name: weapon_knife_flip
items.item_description: Flip knives sport a Persian-style back-swept blade with an acute point.  While the point itself may be fragile, the overall design of the flip knife's design is surprisingly durable.

items.name: weapon_knife_gut
items.item_description: The most notable feature of a gut knife is the gut hook on the spine of the blade.  Originally popularized as an aid for field dressing game, the gut hook is also effective at  cutting through fibrous materials like rope, webbing, or safety belts with ease.

items.name: weapon_knife_karambit
items.item_description: With its curved blade mimicking a tiger's claw, the karambit was developed as part of the southeast Asian martial discipline of silat. The knife is typically used with a reverse grip, with the finger ring on the index finger.

items.name: weapon_knife_m9_bayonet
items.item_description: This is the M-9 bayonet.  Originally intended to be mounted on a rifle, it is also well suited to close-quarters combat.

items.name: Five Year Service Coin
items.item_description: Has been a member of the Counter-Strike community for over 5 years.

items.name: Community Season One Spring 2013
items.item_description: The Operation Payback event ran from April 25th to September 2nd, 2013 and rewarded community map makers with over $180,000. This pass no longer grants access to an Operation, but may be redeemed for a commemorative Operation Payback Coin.

items.name: Community Season One Spring 2013 Coin 1
items.item_description: Participated in Operation Payback to support community map makers.

items.name: Community Season One Spring 2013 Coin 2
items.item_description: Participated in Operation Payback for 10 hours to support community map makers.

items.name: Community Season One Spring 2013 Coin 3
items.item_description: Participated in Operation Payback for 50 hours to support community map makers.

items.name: Community Season Two Autumn 2013
items.item_description: The Operation Bravo event ran from September 19th, 2013 to February 5th, 2014. This pass no longer grants access to an Operation, but may be redeemed for a commemorative Operation Bravo Coin.

items.name: Community Season Two Autumn 2013 Coin 1
items.item_description: Participated in Operation Bravo.

items.name: Community Season Two Autumn 2013 Coin 2
items.item_description: Participated in Operation Bravo.

items.name: Community Season Two Autumn 2013 Coin 3
items.item_description: Participated in Operation Bravo.

items.name: Community Season Three Spring 2014
items.item_description: Grants access to Operation Phoenix, which consists of access to community maps, exclusive items, and a record of your competitive stats.

items.item_description:
Participated in Operation Phoenix.
Play in Operation Phoenix and win Operation Phoenix Competitive Matches to upgrade this coin.

items.name: Name Tag
items.item_description: This item will rename a weapon. A custom engraved nameplate will be applied to the weapon and viewable in game.

items.name: Weapon Case Key
items.item_description: This key will open any Valve Series Weapon Case. Non-Valve Series cases (e.g. eSports Case) require their own key to open.

items.name: E-Sports Weapon Case Key 1
items.item_description:
This key opens any eSports Case.

A portion of the proceeds from the sale of this key will go towards one of the established community-run CS:GO tournaments. Stay tuned for further announcements.

items.name: Sticker
items.item_description: This sticker can be applied to any weapon you own and can be scraped to look more worn. You can scrape the same sticker multiple times, making it a bit more worn each time, until it is removed from the weapon.

items.name: Gift - 1 Player
items.item_description: When used, a random player in your match will get a random item as a gift from you.

items.name: Gift - 9 Players
items.item_description: When used, up to 9 other players in your match will get a random item as a gift from you.

items.name: Sticker Crate Key
items.item_description: This key will open any Valve Series Capsule.

items.name: Community Case Key 1
items.item_description: This key only opens Winter Offensive Cases

items.name: Gift - 25 Spectators
items.item_description: When used, up to 25 viewers watching your match will get a random item as a gift from you.

items.name: Community Case Key 2
items.item_description: This key only opens Operation Phoenix Cases
